Build a console-based Jewelry Inventory Manager using Java ArrayList to track gold/silver items,
quantities, and rates—perfect for your shop app prototype.
This project practices ArrayList operations like add, remove, update, search, and sort while
handling real business logic.

Project Overview
Create an InventoryManager class with an ArrayList of JewelryItem
objects (name, type like "Gold Ring", quantity, price per gram, total value).
Include a menu for add/view/update/remove/search/sort low-stock items. Use Scanner for input
and run in a loop until exit.

Key features:

Add new items dynamically.

Display all or filtered (e.g., low stock <10).
